==English==

===Etymology===
:Comes from Greek ''[[amethystos]]'' meaning "not drunken", from ''[[methu]]'' meaning [[wine]]. The Greeks believed that the amethyst prevented [[intoxication]].

===Noun===
'''amethyst'''  (''plural'' '''[[amethysts]]''')

# A [[transparent]] [[purple]] variety of [[quartz]], used as a [[gemstone]].
# A [[purple]] [[colour]].
